verbose_text: The trial included five male and five female patients, with a median age of 40 years (range, 28-49 years), who were categorized as high-risk AML mainly based on the higher expression levels of WT1 at initial diagnosis [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR] and received an allogeneic sibling donor HSCT followed by anti-leukemic WT1-CTLs infusion.
